s, (120), octobre, p. 177-193.<br /> - Olivier Godard (2011), Climate justice, between global and international justice - Insights from justification theory. San Domenico di Fiesole (Italy), Global Governance Programme-11, Robert Schuman Centre For Advanced Studies – European University Institute<em>, EUI Working Papers</em> - RSCAS 2011/56, November, (46 p.). http://hdl.handle.net/1814/19157<br /> - Olivier Godard (2012), &quot;Managing Global Risks Through ‘Proportionate’ Precaution: the Interplay between States, Civil Society and International Regulation&quot;, in E. Brousseau, T. Dedeurwaerdere and B. Siebenhüner (eds.),<em> Reflexive Governance for Global Public Goods</em>. Cambridge (MA), MIT Press, Series “Politics, Science, and the Environment”, p. 123-143.<br /> - Olivier Godard (2012), &quot;Expertise scientifique d’enjeux collectifs et décision publique&quot; in P.-A. Chardel, C. Gossart et B. Reber (dir.),<em> Conflits des interprétations dans la société de l’information. Éthique et politique de l’environnement</em>. Paris, Hermès Science Publications - Lavoisier, p. 179-203.<br /> - Olivier Godard (2012), &quot;Le climato-scepticisme médiatique en France : un sophisme moderne&quot;,<em> Revue Écologie &amp; Politique</em>, 2012-2 (45), p. 47-69.<br /> - Olivier Godard (2012), Ecological debt and historical responsibility revisited – The case of climate change. San Domenico di Fiesole (Italy), Global Governance Programme-11, Robert Schuman Centre For Advanced Studies – European University Institute,<em> EUI Working Papers</em> - RSCAS 2012/46, September, (24 p.). http://hdl.handle.net/1814/23430 <br /> - Jean-Philippe Barde &amp; Olivier Godard (2012), “Chapter 3. Economic Principles of Environmental Fiscal Reform”, in J.E. Milne &amp; M. S. Andersen (eds), <em>Handbook of Research on Environmental Taxation.</em> Cheltenham (UK) and Northampton (MA, US), Edward Elgar Publishing, p. 33-58.<br /> - Olivier Godard (2012), &quot;La politique des risques peut